.TH SPLIT 1 
.SH NAME
split \- split a file into pieces
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B split
[
.B \-\fIn
]
[ file [ name ] ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Split
reads
.I file
and writes
it in
.IR n -line
pieces
(default 1000 lines)
onto
a set of output files.  The name of the first output
file is
.I name
with
.B aa
appended, and so on
lexicographically,
up to
.B zz
(a maximum of 676 files).
.I Name
cannot be longer than 12 characters.
If no output name is given,
.B x
is default.
.PP
If no input file is given, or
if
.B \-
is given in its stead,
then the standard input file is used.
.SH SEE ALSO
bfs(1), csplit(1).
